<TITLE> Victory Day security will be tight: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 26 (bdnews24.com)  The government has taken ample measures to ensure safety during Victory Day celebrations on Dec 16, home secretary Abdul Karim said on Wednesday. "All possible steps pertaining to law and order, including two-tier security measures, have been finalised to ensure the smooth and disciplined celebrations in Dhaka city, Savar and other areas," he said. Karim briefed reporters, after a meeting on security measures for Victory Day, at the home ministry. Asked if the celebrations would take place amid the emergency, the home secretary said he did not know. "This is a matter of a top-level government decision." Karim said special security measures would cover the main Victory Day venues of Jatiya Smriti Shoudha (National Mausoleum for Martyrs), Bangabhaban, the National Stadium and other areas to be used for receptions, cultural shows and soirees. Construction of gates on the way to Savar would not be allowed on the occasion, he said. Additional police in uniform and plain clothes will be deployed during the official programmes at the national stadium and Savar, Karim added. Traffic police have been instructed to stay alert against the possible traffic congestions and the law and order situation on the day. Home affairs adviser MA Matin chaired the meeting, attended by home secretary Abdul Karim, IGP Nur Muhammad, RAB director general Hasan Mahmud Khandaker and representatives from different ministries and departments. b
